# Lab Setup

## Objective

Build an enterprise Active Directory homelab using Windows Server 2022 and VMware Workstation to develop hands-on experience with identity management, user administration, resource access, and enterprise infrastructure concepts.

---

## Environment

### Virtualization Platform

* VMware Workstation

### Server

| Component        | Value                        |
| ---------------- | ---------------------------- |
| Hostname         | DC01                         |
| Operating System | Windows Server 2022 Standard |
| Role             | Domain Controller            |

### Domain

```text
gallegos.local
```

---

## Network Configuration

| Setting         | Value         |
| --------------- | ------------- |
| IP Address      | 192.168.10.10 |
| Subnet Mask     | 255.255.255.0 |
| Default Gateway | 192.168.10.1  |
| DNS Server      | 192.168.10.10 |

---

## Installed Roles

The following Windows Server roles were installed and configured:

* Active Directory Domain Services (AD DS)
* DNS Server
* DHCP Server

---

## Organizational Units

The following Organizational Units (OUs) were created to organize users, computers, and resources:

* IT
* HR
* Sales
* Workstations
* Servers

---

## Lab Architecture

```text
DC01 (192.168.10.10)
│
├── Active Directory
├── DNS
├── DHCP
├── Users & Groups
└── File Shares
```

---

## Validation

The following configuration tasks were successfully completed:

* Installed Windows Server 2022
* Assigned a static IP address
* Installed AD DS, DNS, and DHCP roles
* Promoted the server to a Domain Controller
* Created the gallegos.local domain
* Created Organizational Units
* Verified Active Directory functionality

---

## Skills Demonstrated

* Windows Server Administration
* Active Directory Administration
* DNS Configuration
* DHCP Configuration
* Network Configuration
* Virtualization
* Enterprise Infrastructure Deployment

---

## Purpose

This environment simulates a small enterprise infrastructure used for identity management, access control, resource administration, and centralized authentication.

The lab serves as the foundation for future projects involving Group Policy, Windows administration, security monitoring, networking, and enterprise system management.
